w, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when an event-time timer fires\n4. `void onMerge(W window, OnMergeContext ctx)` - Called when windows are merged (requires `canMerge()` to return true)\n\nAdditional methods:\n- `boolean canMerge()` - Default returns false; override and return true if the trigger supports merging\n- `void clear(W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Clears any state maintained by the trigger for a window\n\n## Reference Implementation: EventTimeSessionWindows\nFile: `flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/EventTimeSessionWindows.java`\n\nThis `MergingWindowAssigner<Object, TimeWindow>` implementation demonstrates the pattern:\n- `assignWindows()` creates a single `TimeWindow(timestamp, timestamp + sessionTimeout)` for each element\n- `mergeWindows()` delegates to the static utility `TimeWindow.mergeWindows(windows, c)` which handles overlapping window merging\n- `getDefaultTrigger()` returns `EventTimeTrigger.create()`\n- `isEventTime()` returns true\n- `getWindowSerializer()` returns `new TimeWindow.Serializer()`\n\n## TimeWindow Output Type\nFile: `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/windows/TimeWindow.java`\n\nThe concrete `TimeWindow` class represents time intervals:\n- Constructor: `TimeWindow(long start, long end)` where end is exclusive\n- Key accessors: `getStart()` and `getEnd()`\n- Utility methods: `intersects(TimeWindow other)` and `cover(TimeWindow other)` for merging logic\n- Static utility: `mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c)` implements the overlapping window merge algorithm used by session assigners\n\nThis architecture enables developers to create custom window assigners by implementing the `assignWindows()` method, and optionally extend `MergingWindowAssigner` and implement `mergeWindows()` for session-style semantics."
